When we had our first dates...

724
00:54:05,250 --> 00:54:06,958
...you were going out with me

725
00:54:07,042 --> 00:54:08,583
'cause you were getting
material gains later.

726
00:54:08,667 --> 00:54:11,833
Is that true?

727
00:54:12,417 --> 00:54:13,583
Yes, it is.

728
00:54:15,667 --> 00:54:18,042
...but that was just
the beginning.

729
00:54:18,125 --> 00:54:21,167
Then I started fighting with myself.

730
00:54:21,250 --> 00:54:23,000
Something was happening inside me.

731
00:54:23,083 --> 00:54:27,792
A woman's feelings, new to me.
I wanted to stop them.

732
00:54:28,708 --> 00:54:30,667
Who said that?

733
00:54:30,750 --> 00:54:33,625
Rasho, stop eating.

734
00:54:33,708 --> 00:54:34,708
Translate.

735
00:54:35,750 --> 00:54:36,750
Quiet.

736
00:54:38,708 --> 00:54:42,250
So then
I started getting scared.

737
00:54:44,917 --> 00:54:46,167
Scared of what?

738
00:54:48,125 --> 00:54:49,708
Scared of my feelings for you.

739
00:54:49,792 --> 00:54:51,125
Who is saying that?

740
00:54:51,208 --> 00:54:54,792
I don't understand.

741
00:55:07,625 --> 00:55:09,083
Rasho, what's going on?

742
00:55:09,167 --> 00:55:10,375
It's over.

743
00:55:12,250 --> 00:55:17,792
They are not talking anymore.

744
00:55:29,083 --> 00:55:30,500
- What's wrong?
- Um...

745
00:55:31,167 --> 00:55:32,458
Nothing.

746
00:55:32,542 --> 00:55:35,542
Could you wait for me downstairs, please?

747
00:55:36,875 --> 00:55:40,792
Downstairs? Alone? With those people?

748
00:55:42,208 --> 00:55:43,667
Please, Aaron, I...

749
00:55:44,417 --> 00:55:45,833
It's time for my ritual.

750
00:55:45,917 --> 00:55:47,708
I can't miss it.

751
00:55:50,417 --> 00:55:51,625
I'm sorry.

752
00:55:52,417 --> 00:55:53,402
Okay.

753
00:55:53,417 --> 00:55:54,917
- Okay?
- Yeah.

754
00:55:55,708 --> 00:55:59,333
Wait. Hurry! He's coming.

755
00:55:59,417 --> 00:56:00,708
He's coming.

756
00:56:08,458 --> 00:56:09,458
Hurry up!

757
00:56:10,458 --> 00:56:11,500
Get aside!

758
00:56:21,250 --> 00:56:24,208
Any ideas?

759
00:56:25,875 --> 00:56:27,333
Only the one I was worried about.

760
00:56:28,000 --> 00:56:29,500
- Maybe we should...
- I'm going.

761
00:56:43,083 --> 00:56:45,292
I'll open his back pocket
and you get whatever is in it.

762
00:56:45,375 --> 00:56:46,375
Hey!

763
00:56:47,958 --> 00:56:50,667
Hey!
Get away from him.

764
00:57:03,500 --> 00:57:06,458
Aaron?
Aaron, are you alright?

765
00:57:08,208 --> 00:57:09,208
Oh.

766
00:57:13,333 --> 00:57:14,417
What's up, man?

767
00:57:15,000 --> 00:57:16,250
Hey, what's up, man?

768
00:57:29,833 --> 00:57:32,000
My sister dragged you into this,
didn't she?

769
00:57:35,500 --> 00:57:36,792
Oh, man.

770
00:57:38,792 --> 00:57:40,083
Hey, Doc.

771
00:57:40,167 --> 00:57:41,958
Aaron! Jesus!

772
00:57:42,042 --> 00:57:44,208
No, no, no. It's not what it looks like.

773
00:57:44,292 --> 00:57:47,292
I, uh... I, um... I'm completely sane.

774
00:57:47,375 --> 00:57:50,000
I don't know what happened.
I think I lost consciousness.

775
00:57:50,083 --> 00:57:52,000
Maybe someone tried
to rob me or something.

776
00:57:52,667 --> 00:57:55,167
<i>- It's okay.</i>
- Let me refresh your memory.

777
00:57:55,250 --> 00:57:57,625
I received all of these saying,
"What's up, Doc?"

778
00:58:01,167 --> 00:58:03,000
Shit!

779
00:58:03,083 --> 00:58:04,667
Exactly.

780
00:58:04,750 --> 00:58:06,792
<i>Who takes a selfie with a tiger rug?</i>

781
00:58:07,958 --> 00:58:11,125
<i>And to answer your question,
"How did I lose consciousness?"</i>

782
00:58:11,208 --> 00:58:15,250
Aaron, you know we have to report
to your parole officer every month.

783
00:58:15,333 --> 00:58:16,500
What do I say to him now?

784
00:58:16,583 --> 00:58:18,042
There she is.

785
00:58:18,125 --> 00:58:21,083
Uh, Doc, I gotta go.

786
00:58:21,167 --> 00:58:22,792
No, no, Aaron, don't hang up, okay?

787
00:58:22,875 --> 00:58:24,917
This shit is serious. More than you think.

788
00:58:26,000 --> 00:58:28,750
Rasho, is there
something you're not telling me?

789
00:58:28,833 --> 00:58:32,542
I gave him something to drink.

790
00:58:32,625 --> 00:58:34,333
From your poison?

791
00:58:34,417 --> 00:58:36,500
My whiskey is better than Johnny.

792
00:58:36,583 --> 00:58:38,917
We've poisoned him!

793
00:58:40,083 --> 00:58:41,833
You ditched him with the gypsies?
Are you insane?

794
00:58:41,917 --> 00:58:44,625
- Bobby.
- He's a fighter, what could have...

795
00:58:44,708 --> 00:58:47,417
They got him drunk
with bootlegged whiskey.

796
00:58:47,500 --> 00:58:48,917
I can't believe he's still alive.

797
00:58:49,000 --> 00:58:50,542
Aaron, I'm sorry.

798
00:58:50,625 --> 00:58:52,167
- I shouldn't have...
- It's okay!

799
00:58:52,250 --> 00:58:55,083
Actually, I was, I was having fun
until I passed out in the mud.

800
00:58:55,167 --> 00:58:57,292
Aaron, please, I wanna talk to my sister.

801
00:59:00,958 --> 00:59:02,583
You don't realise how...

802
00:59:03,708 --> 00:59:05,917
You don't realise
how important is this fight for us.

803
00:59:06,000 --> 00:59:07,250
I want you to call it off.

804
00:59:07,333 --> 00:59:10,458
What?

805
00:59:10,542 --> 00:59:12,625
For you it might be good,
but it's not for Aaron.

806
00:59:13,208 --> 00:59:15,375
So you care more about him now?

807
00:59:15,458 --> 00:59:18,417
He's doing it for us!
I've never met anyone like him.

808
00:59:18,500 --> 00:59:20,875
Go to a mental institution, there's sure
to be a lot of people like him.

809
00:59:20,958 --> 00:59:23,375
Don't you dare say that!

810
00:59:23,458 --> 00:59:25,792
I won't allow you to call him crazy.
He's not. I'm not.

811
00:59:28,500 --> 00:59:29,917
- Jana...
- Bobby!

812
00:59:30,000 --> 00:59:31,708
Now is not the right time.

813
00:59:31,792 --> 00:59:33,500
- Bobby!
- Michael, please shut up.

814
00:59:33,583 --> 00:59:34,583
Bobby.

815
00:59:35,042 --> 00:59:38,667
I sold the TV rights for the fight,
pay-per-view, motherfucker!

816
00:59:42,625 --> 00:59:45,125
- Wait. Wait.
- Yes.

817
01:00:05,292 --> 01:00:07,583
Hey!

818
01:00:24,042 --> 01:00:26,375
The news with the bike
was all over the net.

819
01:00:26,458 --> 01:00:31,042
Then the Bulgarian MMA federation
wanted Aaron to go to psychiatric test

820
01:00:31,125 --> 01:00:33,500
just to determine
whether he's sane or not.

821
01:00:34,042 --> 01:00:35,375
They could've just asked me.

822
01:00:36,125 --> 01:00:37,417
Anyway, there's no such test,

823
01:00:37,500 --> 01:00:39,750
they just wanted to make sure
I was gonna play by their rules.

824
01:00:39,833 --> 01:00:40,833
Aaron, please.

825
01:00:41,333 --> 01:00:44,500
Act like you're not crazy. Okay?

826
01:00:46,625 --> 01:00:47,750
Mr. Hunter,

827
01:00:47,833 --> 01:00:50,208
my apologies, I heard you have
had issues with your memory.

828
01:00:50,292 --> 01:00:53,208
I have a few questions
regarding the MMA rules

829
01:00:53,292 --> 01:00:55,292
and your motivation
to take part in this fight.

830
01:00:56,042 --> 01:01:00,083
Mr. Hunter, my apologies,
but I heard there's some memory issues.

831
01:01:00,167 --> 01:01:02,792
And I wanna ask about MMA fight rules.

832
01:01:03,500 --> 01:01:07,083
What are the forbidden
actions and hits during a fight?

833
01:01:07,167 --> 01:01:10,000
Alright, the forbidden hits and punches?

834
01:01:11,083 --> 01:01:13,500
The fighter isn't allowed
to pull the opponent's hair,

835
01:01:13,583 --> 01:01:15,125
no pokes in the eyes.

836
01:01:15,208 --> 01:01:18,917
No hits below the belt,
no kicking when the opponent is down.

837
01:01:19,458 --> 01:01:22,583
No punching in the back of the head,
no short rabbit punches.

838
01:01:36,458 --> 01:01:39,167
How many rounds are there
in the fight and how long do they last?

839
01:01:39,250 --> 01:01:41,583
How many rounds
and how many minutes?

840
01:01:41,667 --> 01:01:43,000
Three rounds, five minutes each.

841
01:01:45,542 --> 01:01:47,792
In which cases
does the fight finish?

842
01:01:47,875 --> 01:01:49,667
What are the cases?

843
01:01:50,875 --> 01:01:52,375
When the fighter taps out,

844
01:01:52,458 --> 01:01:54,917
or when the referee decides
he has to stop the fight.

845
01:01:55,000 --> 01:01:59,333
Why did you decide to make
your comeback here in Bulgaria?

846
01:01:59,417 --> 01:02:03,750
Why did you decide
to make your comeback here in Bulgaria?

847
01:02:05,542 --> 01:02:07,333
I was, uh...

848
01:02:07,417 --> 01:02:10,333
I was in the car with... with Bobby.

849
01:02:10,417 --> 01:02:14,000
And, uh... a song came on the radio.

850
01:02:14,667 --> 01:02:15,667
And, uh...

851
01:02:17,375 --> 01:02:18,792
Uh, Harold Melvin.

852
01:02:19,833 --> 01:02:23,333
I told Bobby that if he would sing
the song with me,

853
01:02:23,417 --> 01:02:25,000
then I will do the fight.

854
01:02:25,583 --> 01:02:26,917
Um...

855
01:02:27,000 --> 01:02:28,958
Oh, sorry, that's all I remember.

856
01:02:32,000 --> 01:02:37,375
Uh, I noticed that
the sport is progressing quickly here.

857
01:02:37,458 --> 01:02:41,167
And that Bobby has great potential.

858
01:02:41,250 --> 01:02:46,708
I told Harold Melvin,
my former coach and ex-MMA fighter,

859
01:02:46,792 --> 01:02:52,042
that he would be the best opponent.

860
01:02:52,125 --> 01:02:53,958
- Exactly.
- Yes.

861
01:02:54,750 --> 01:02:57,458
I've never heard of
a fighter named Harold Melvin.

862
01:02:57,542 --> 01:03:00,667
I hadn't either,
but I didn't want to insult him.

863
01:03:12,292 --> 01:03:15,833
* <i>So come down and satisfy
The need in me</i> *

864
01:03:15,917 --> 01:03:18,583
* <i>'Cause only your good loving
Can set me free</i> *

865
01:03:21,208 --> 01:03:23,042
Why the hell did you have to be so honest?

866
01:03:23,125 --> 01:03:24,708
You wanted me to lie?

867
01:03:24,792 --> 01:03:26,833
Yes, that's what normal people do.

868
01:03:26,917 --> 01:03:28,167
I'm not normal.

869
01:03:28,250 --> 01:03:30,875
Shit.

870
01:03:30,958 --> 01:03:31,958
Now we're screwed.

871
01:03:35,417 --> 01:03:38,500
<i>* I can see wrong and right
Never choose a side *</i>

872
01:03:39,042 --> 01:03:41,417
<i>* Runnin' on red, not black and white *</i>

873
01:03:41,500 --> 01:03:42,958
<i>* Grey is where I hide *</i>

874
01:03:43,042 --> 01:03:45,375
<i>* I'm always busy *</i>

875
01:03:45,458 --> 01:03:47,208
<i>* When they all need me *</i>

876
01:03:47,833 --> 01:03:50,042
<i>* I wanna do it *</i>

877
01:03:50,125 --> 01:03:51,833
<i>* But I'm always gone *</i>

878
01:03:52,667 --> 01:03:54,625
<i>* I wanna fight it *</i>

879
01:03:56,792 --> 01:03:58,792
- Aaron!
- He's busy.

880
01:03:58,875 --> 01:04:02,167
- I'll talk to you, too. Aaron!
- What you've come for won't happen.

881
01:04:02,250 --> 01:04:05,542
You really think I came all this way
to this shithole for you to tell me.

882
01:04:05,625 --> 01:04:07,250
You're from fucking Albania!

883
01:04:07,333 --> 01:04:08,417
If we reach an agreement,

884
01:04:08,500 --> 01:04:10,792
I'll sign the papers
and forget about the lawsuit.

885
01:04:10,875 --> 01:04:14,292
Why? You're still his wife.
You'll take half of his earnings, anyway.

886
01:04:14,375 --> 01:04:16,042
- Don't waste my time.
- What do you want?

887
01:04:16,125 --> 01:04:17,417
I know you'll twist things around,

888
01:04:17,500 --> 01:04:20,375
- so everything ends up in your account.
- What do you want? What do you want?

889
01:04:20,458 --> 01:04:22,750
I know everything is possible
in this country.

890
01:04:25,167 --> 01:04:28,250
I want an equal partner's share.

891
01:04:28,333 --> 01:04:29,625
Equal? Partner share?

892
01:04:30,208 --> 01:04:31,458
No way, that's not happening.

893
01:04:31,542 --> 01:04:32,792
- No way?
- Yes. No way.

894
01:04:33,917 --> 01:04:35,458
- I can go lower.
- How lower?

895
01:04:36,375 --> 01:04:39,333
I can go lower if you tell me
you made him sign the insurance.

896
01:04:40,542 --> 01:04:43,042
I cannot promise you
he's gonna sign the insurance.

897
01:04:43,125 --> 01:04:45,833
And regarding the cut,
you need to talk to my other partner.

898
01:04:50,583 --> 01:04:53,333
Aaron's opponent is your business partner?

899
01:04:54,083 --> 01:04:55,083
Yes.

900
01:05:02,000 --> 01:05:03,750
- Aaron.
- Oh, God!

901
01:05:04,875 --> 01:05:07,833
She's got what he has.
Not the same thing, Michael,

902
01:05:07,917 --> 01:05:10,458
- but it looks like that.
- It's not the same. Similar.

903
01:05:10,542 --> 01:05:12,917
I'm sorry, I didn't mean to just...

904
01:05:13,000 --> 01:05:14,833
- Hi, Aaron.
- Evelyn?

905
01:05:16,208 --> 01:05:20,667
I was wondering why here
or why this place, but, uh...

906
01:05:21,208 --> 01:05:24,500
Now I know,
and I'm happy for you, honestly.

907
01:05:25,917 --> 01:05:27,125
What are you doing here?

908
01:05:27,792 --> 01:05:29,000
Uh, I mean...

909
01:05:29,083 --> 01:05:31,542
I'm trying to help, I guess.

910
01:05:31,625 --> 01:05:35,667
And I, I see that you're in love
and the two of you have this thing...

911
01:05:36,333 --> 01:05:38,333
Excuse me, how did she get it?

912
01:05:38,417 --> 01:05:40,583
She doesn't look like
an ex-fighter.

913
01:05:41,917 --> 01:05:43,917
Oh, sorry. I'm sorry, dear.

914
01:05:44,000 --> 01:05:46,708
How rude of me
to not even introduced myself.

915
01:05:46,792 --> 01:05:47,917
I'm Evelyn, his wife...

916
01:05:49,042 --> 01:05:50,292
Oh, fuck.

917
01:05:50,375 --> 01:05:52,667
I, I'm sorry. I didn't... I forgot!

918
01:05:52,750 --> 01:05:54,833
- Evelyn, stop. Stop.
- The touching and...

919
01:05:54,917 --> 01:05:56,875
Listen. What...

920
01:05:56,958 --> 01:06:00,917
We could fix this, whatever you want.
I mean, um... You want me to sign something?

921
01:06:01,000 --> 01:06:02,667
- Okay...
- No, no. Easy, easy.

922
01:06:03,792 --> 01:06:08,375
The important thing is that
we get the best out of this fight.

923
01:06:09,250 --> 01:06:10,250
- Yeah.
- Right?

924
01:06:10,333 --> 01:06:12,167
Wow.

925
01:06:13,583 --> 01:06:18,500
I don't know what to say.
You haven't sounded like this in years.

926
01:06:20,417 --> 01:06:21,417
Right.

927
01:06:22,333 --> 01:06:25,375
I guess, I'm, uh... I'm almost normal.

928
01:06:26,917 --> 01:06:27,917
Yeah.

929
01:06:43,500 --> 01:06:45,792
Well, that's the other problem you have.

930
01:06:46,833 --> 01:06:48,625
That was his sister.

931
01:06:50,583 --> 01:06:51,583
Hey.

932
01:06:52,375 --> 01:06:55,500
I came to apologise,
but the timing was bad.

933
01:06:55,583 --> 01:06:56,958
Oh. It's all right.

934
01:06:58,292 --> 01:07:01,125
Yesterday,
I looked a guy right in the eyes.

935
01:07:01,208 --> 01:07:03,417
When he walked past me,
we almost touched shoulders.

936
01:07:04,125 --> 01:07:05,667
You're still taking your pills?

937
01:07:05,750 --> 01:07:07,417
Yeah, I think that's the reason.

938
01:07:07,500 --> 01:07:09,167
You won't quit the fight, right?

939
01:07:09,250 --> 01:07:10,193
No.

940
01:07:10,208 --> 01:07:12,458
It's a win-win for all of us,
you know that.

941
01:07:12,542 --> 01:07:15,042
That's the only reason
I had to act like that with Evelyn...

942
01:07:15,125 --> 01:07:17,375
And become like them.

943
01:07:17,458 --> 01:07:18,667
No, I'm getting better.

944
01:07:19,708 --> 01:07:21,750
- You're just losing yourself.
- No.

945
01:07:22,333 --> 01:07:24,542
Oh! Gosh.

946
01:07:24,625 --> 01:07:26,333
Are you okay?

947
01:07:27,167 --> 01:07:29,083
Jana, what happened?

948
01:07:29,167 --> 01:07:33,042
I hit the lamppost, Dad.
Nothing new.

949
01:07:40,208 --> 01:07:42,125
I'll drive you
to the pharmacy.

950
01:07:42,208 --> 01:07:43,792
We got
to get her checked out.

951
01:07:43,875 --> 01:07:45,667
Just me. Aaron stays.

952
01:07:57,875 --> 01:07:58,875
Hey.

953
01:08:00,792 --> 01:08:03,875
Don't follow.
We are different now.

954
01:08:21,417 --> 01:08:26,667
<i>* Another world is an open door
And I feel no love *</i>

955
01:08:29,708 --> 01:08:35,042
<i>* Another world is a lonely road
