01:09:11,917 --> 01:09:13,000
Mr. Hunter?

963
01:09:15,333 --> 01:09:16,667
I asked you a question.

964
01:09:20,708 --> 01:09:23,208
I'm sorry, I...
I was thinking about something else.

965
01:09:25,375 --> 01:09:27,167
Why did you accept this fight?

966
01:09:27,750 --> 01:09:30,708
Well, I said I'd do the fight
to help out Bobby and his family.

967
01:09:33,208 --> 01:09:35,292
You agreed to do this fight

968
01:09:35,375 --> 01:09:37,583
in order to help your opponent
and his family?

969
01:09:37,667 --> 01:09:40,583
I'm sorry, man. I know...
I... I shouldn't have said...

970
01:09:40,667 --> 01:09:42,250
- Aaron...
- Mr. Hunter.

971
01:09:42,333 --> 01:09:44,833
No, it's just that we didn't rehearse
this part... the question.

972
01:09:44,917 --> 01:09:46,875
The conversation
is only between the two of us.

973
01:09:46,958 --> 01:09:48,167
- Take it easy.
- It's okay.

974
01:09:49,625 --> 01:09:51,833
Hey, just answer
the question, Aaron.

975
01:09:51,917 --> 01:09:53,833
Can you please answer my question?

976
01:09:54,917 --> 01:09:56,833
You agreed to do this fight

977
01:09:56,917 --> 01:10:00,125
in order to help
your opponent and his family?

978
01:10:08,375 --> 01:10:10,125
I didn't want to do it for myself.

979
01:10:16,625 --> 01:10:18,208
Me and Bobby, we're a lot alike,

980
01:10:19,708 --> 01:10:24,542
only I've been able to achieve
almost everything he's always wanted.

981
01:10:26,000 --> 01:10:27,625
And it came easy for me.

982
01:10:31,167 --> 01:10:33,500
I didn't even enjoy my success.

983
01:10:36,458 --> 01:10:37,583
I keep thinking that...

984
01:10:39,208 --> 01:10:41,083
I've gotten way too much out of life.

985
01:10:42,375 --> 01:10:44,500
That's why I keep living with this...

986
01:10:45,917 --> 01:10:47,458
sense of guilt.

987
01:10:50,875 --> 01:10:55,000
So I figured, uh... in order to feel good,

988
01:10:55,583 --> 01:10:58,417
I should not do it for myself.

989
01:11:00,250 --> 01:11:03,417
I need to do something for someone else.

990
01:11:08,958 --> 01:11:10,708
And I've achieved a lot.

991
01:11:10,792 --> 01:11:13,958
But, hey, listen,
I never really had a family.

992
01:11:15,000 --> 01:11:16,333
And since I've been...

993
01:11:19,375 --> 01:11:20,542
Since I've come here...

994
01:11:25,125 --> 01:11:27,542
I started feeling something
very close to that.

995
01:11:31,833 --> 01:11:34,083
I guess you know I forget stuff.

996
01:11:36,417 --> 01:11:38,750
Big chunks of my life are...

997
01:11:40,667 --> 01:11:41,708
missing.

998
01:11:43,208 --> 01:11:46,625
People say your memory is what makes you...

999
01:11:48,917 --> 01:11:49,917
what you are.

1000
01:11:51,208 --> 01:11:52,417
That, uh...

1001
01:11:53,417 --> 01:11:55,625
That's the reason to keep living.

1002
01:12:00,417 --> 01:12:03,583
If I can't remember, at least...

1003
01:12:04,667 --> 01:12:08,625
at least I have people around
that remember me.

1004
01:12:35,625 --> 01:12:37,750
Life. Nothing else.

1005
01:12:37,833 --> 01:12:39,917
Work accident, injury, life.

1006
01:12:40,000 --> 01:12:42,292
Michael, tell me what I don't know,
or I swear...

1007
01:12:42,375 --> 01:12:43,833
Aaron has punch-drunk syndrome.

1008
01:12:45,000 --> 01:12:48,125
He takes pills for Alzheimer's,
but it's damaging his brain...

1009
01:12:48,208 --> 01:12:50,625
- I know what it is, Michael.
- What do you want from me?

1010
01:12:52,917 --> 01:12:54,708
For 15 years, I've been his nanny.

1011
01:12:55,292 --> 01:12:58,042
I have no life. I have nobody.

1012
01:12:58,125 --> 01:13:01,792
He couldn't do anything without me.
Then he blows it all to shit.

1013
01:13:02,583 --> 01:13:04,917
I lost everything I got.

1014
01:13:06,250 --> 01:13:08,958
No one wanted to hire me
after what happened to Aaron.

1015
01:13:09,792 --> 01:13:13,208
And right now, I'm just a babysitter
to a retarded kid.

1016
01:13:13,292 --> 01:13:14,292
Don't say that.

1017
01:13:14,375 --> 01:13:16,167
- You don't know what it's like.
- I don't?

1018
01:13:16,250 --> 01:13:17,833
- You don't.
- I don't know what it's like?

1019
01:13:17,917 --> 01:13:18,917
Bobby, stop it.

1020
01:13:20,625 --> 01:13:22,708
The chances of that happening are minimal.

1021
01:13:24,292 --> 01:13:27,833
Look, me and Michael,
we gave our lives to Aaron.

1022
01:13:28,875 --> 01:13:30,917
Don't you think
if something happened to him,

1023
01:13:31,000 --> 01:13:33,833
we don't deserve to get any recognition
for our efforts?

1024
01:13:34,500 --> 01:13:35,708
Recognition?

1025
01:13:35,792 --> 01:13:39,083
You could always end the fight
by submitting him or something.

1026
01:13:39,167 --> 01:13:40,750
He would remember to tap out?

1027
01:13:42,125 --> 01:13:43,542
You think he's that rational?

1028
01:14:04,125 --> 01:14:05,792
I came from the hall.

1029
01:14:06,917 --> 01:14:10,417
Aaron is... I don't know how to...

1030
01:14:10,500 --> 01:14:14,458
I want to have nothing
to do with this anymore.

1031
01:14:15,667 --> 01:14:16,667
Uh-huh.

1032
01:14:20,000 --> 01:14:23,375
Remember what your grandma
used to tell me when you were little?

1033
01:14:24,750 --> 01:14:25,750
She used to say,

1034
01:14:26,625 --> 01:14:31,083
"Why do you want to punish her?
She is in her own world."

1035
01:14:32,958 --> 01:14:34,583
How do you know that's wrong there?

1036
01:14:37,292 --> 01:14:42,417
How do you know about his? Or ours?

1037
01:14:53,792 --> 01:14:55,625
What's wrong? Why are you sitting?

1038
01:14:55,708 --> 01:14:57,542
- Don't know. It's all good.
- Ah.

1039
01:14:58,750 --> 01:15:00,208
Why are you so stiff?
Do I have to deal with you too now?

1040
01:15:00,292 --> 01:15:01,417
What do you mean?

1041
01:15:01,500 --> 01:15:04,042
Doesn't matter. Come on!

1042
01:15:11,917 --> 01:15:15,417
- Faster! What are you?
- What am I?

1043
01:15:15,500 --> 01:15:17,458
- What?
- What am I?

1044
01:15:17,542 --> 01:15:20,208
You are a state champion! Say it!

1045
01:15:20,292 --> 01:15:22,333
- I'm a champion.
- Louder!

1046
01:15:22,417 --> 01:15:25,750
- I'm a champion.
- Louder!

1047
01:15:26,875 --> 01:15:29,833
- I'm a champion.
- Louder!

1048
01:15:34,250 --> 01:15:36,042
- I'm a mean motherfucker!
- I'm a mean motherfucker!

1049
01:15:45,167 --> 01:15:47,833
- I'll destroy anyone who comes in my way!
- I will destroy anyone...

1050
01:15:53,917 --> 01:15:57,125
- I'm a terminator!
- I'm a terminator!

1051
01:17:04,333 --> 01:17:08,750
Ladies and gentlemen,
this is the main event of the evening.

1052
01:17:09,333 --> 01:17:14,042
In the red corner, we have
a fighter with a professional record

1053
01:17:14,125 --> 01:17:19,875
of seven wins, two losses
and one no contest.

1054
01:17:19,958 --> 01:17:22,708
Fighting out of Bansko, Bulgaria,

1055
01:17:22,792 --> 01:17:25,458
Borislav "Good Night" Tumbev!

1056
01:17:27,542 --> 01:17:28,792
In the blue corner,

1057
01:17:28,875 --> 01:17:33,042
please, give it up for the fighter
with the professional record

1058
01:17:33,125 --> 01:17:36,208
of 52 wins and only eight defeats.

1059
01:17:36,292 --> 01:17:40,542
The MMA legend,
fighting out of Brooklyn, New York,

1060
01:17:40,625 --> 01:17:44,250
Aaron "Lionheart" Hunter!

1061
01:17:47,250 --> 01:17:51,250
Good evening, ladies and gentlemen.
Our tale of the tape is here.

1062
01:17:51,958 --> 01:17:56,042
As you can see, Hunter is taller
and has a slight reach advantage.

1063
01:17:56,125 --> 01:17:57,917
Tumbev is ten years younger, though.

1064
01:17:58,542 --> 01:18:01,250
Yes,
but that doesn't help his Efbet odds.

1065
01:18:01,333 --> 01:18:04,375
Six to one for him being the underdog
and Hunter the favourite.

1066
01:18:06,167 --> 01:18:07,875
Fighters, please come up.

1067
01:18:07,958 --> 01:18:11,083
The referee looks like
he's ready to start, but...

1068
01:18:11,167 --> 01:18:14,542
Aaron Hunter seems
a little distracted, don't you think?

1069
01:18:15,167 --> 01:18:17,583
Could he be in love?

1070
01:18:18,958 --> 01:18:21,625
Okay. Protect yourself at all times.

1071
01:18:22,958 --> 01:18:24,500
Follow my instructions.

1072
01:18:26,458 --> 01:18:30,042
If you don't have any questions,
touch gloves,

1073
01:18:30,750 --> 01:18:32,417
and let's go.

1074
01:18:38,542 --> 01:18:40,292
- Fighter, are you ready?
- Yes.

1075
01:18:41,458 --> 01:18:43,000
Fighter, are you ready?

1076
01:18:45,375 --> 01:18:47,458
Fight!

1077
01:18:49,000 --> 01:18:51,125
And the fight is underway!

1078
01:18:57,000 --> 01:18:58,833
Tumbev attacks.

1079
01:18:58,917 --> 01:19:02,250
But Hunter is really acting weird.

1080
01:19:07,375 --> 01:19:08,667
Don't hold back.

1081
01:19:09,500 --> 01:19:10,583
Fight!

1082
01:19:19,375 --> 01:19:20,375
Fight!

1083
01:19:21,542 --> 01:19:25,333
Tumbev! Tumbev! Tumbev!

1084
01:19:55,917 --> 01:19:56,917
Come on!

1085
01:20:12,875 --> 01:20:15,208
Come on, Aaron! Defend yourself!

1086
01:20:15,292 --> 01:20:18,125
Come on, listen to me! Defend yourself.

1087
01:20:31,667 --> 01:20:32,667
Stop.

1088
01:20:33,208 --> 01:20:36,750
And that is the end
of the most devastating round to watch

1089
01:20:36,833 --> 01:20:38,500
in the history of this sport.

1090
01:20:38,583 --> 01:20:40,500
Well, if you're calling this a sport,

1091
01:20:40,583 --> 01:20:42,417
I think you might've been watching
something else.

1092
01:20:45,667 --> 01:20:47,042
Come on, man, fight!

1093
01:20:50,625 --> 01:20:53,125
Hunter is going
to his opponent's corner.

1094
01:20:54,667 --> 01:20:56,667
- Tell me something...
- Aaron, what are you doing?

1095
01:20:56,750 --> 01:20:57,792
Go back.

1096
01:20:57,875 --> 01:20:59,583
It looks like
he's talking to him.

1097
01:20:59,667 --> 01:21:01,458
We have to fight.
We're gonna lose everything.

1098
01:21:01,542 --> 01:21:03,208
- You don't understand...
- Go back! Go back!

1099
01:21:12,208 --> 01:21:15,250
If you don't start
fighting, the people will...

1100
01:21:15,333 --> 01:21:17,417
Want their money back. I know.

1101
01:21:21,250 --> 01:21:23,708
I have never seen
anything like this before.

1102
01:21:23,792 --> 01:21:25,958
I think we'll be seeing that
more than once tonight.

1103
01:21:46,917 --> 01:21:48,667
Aaron?

1104
01:22:14,667 --> 01:22:15,667
Aaron?

1105
01:22:40,542 --> 01:22:42,125
Fight!

1106
01:22:53,250 --> 01:22:56,417
If you don't attack,
this fight will be a no contest.

1107
01:22:57,083 --> 01:22:58,083
Fight.

1108
01:23:20,458 --> 01:23:22,083
Nobody wants to hear you sing, Aaron.

1109
01:23:24,000 --> 01:23:25,667
Evelyn's going to take your money.

1110
01:23:26,875 --> 01:23:28,583
Michael is going to disappear.

1111
01:23:28,667 --> 01:23:31,000
My sister doesn't care about you either!

1112
01:23:32,208 --> 01:23:34,542
So start fighting, you idiot!

1113
01:23:37,292 --> 01:23:40,125
<i>* Don't leave me this way *</i>

1114
01:23:42,417 --> 01:23:46,875
<i>* I can't survive, I can't stay alive *</i>

1115
01:23:46,958 --> 01:23:49,333
<i>* Without your love *</i>

1116
01:23:51,625 --> 01:23:55,542
<i>* Don't leave me this way, no *</i>

1117
01:23:56,625 --> 01:23:58,500
<i>* I can't exist *</i>

1118
01:23:59,500 --> 01:24:03,375
<i>* I'll surely miss your tender kiss *</i>

1119
01:24:04,500 --> 01:24:09,167
<i>* Don't leave me this way, no *</i>

1120
01:24:09,958 --> 01:24:14,333
<i>* Don't leave me this way *</i>

1121
01:24:15,083 --> 01:24:19,750
<i>* I'm a broken man with empty hands *</i>

1122
01:24:20,542 --> 01:24:22,708
<i>* Oh, baby, please, please *</i>

1123
01:24:22,792 --> 01:24:25,875
<i>* Don't leave me this way *</i>

1124
01:24:28,250 --> 01:24:33,375
<i>* Baby, my heart is full of love
And desire for you *</i>

1125
01:24:33,958 --> 01:24:37,417
<i>* Now come on down
And do what you've got to do *</i>

1126
01:24:38,208 --> 01:24:41,875
<i>* You started this fire down in my soul *</i>

1127
01:24:41,958 --> 01:24:45,625
<i>* Now can't you see it's burning
Out of control *</i>

1128
01:24:45,708 --> 01:24:49,000
<i>* Just come down
And satisfy the need in me *</i>

1129
01:24:49,958 --> 01:24:53,333
<i>* 'Cause only your good loving
Can set me free *</i>

1130
01:24:54,333 --> 01:24:55,500
<i>* Free, free *</i>

1131
01:24:56,375 --> 01:24:59,875
<i>* Don't leave me this way *</i>

1132
01:25:01,125 --> 01:25:03,000
<i>* 'Cause it would be wrong *</i>

1133
01:25:04,208 --> 01:25:08,292
<i>* To string along with love so true *</i>

1134
01:25:09,333 --> 01:25:13,333
Ladies and gentlemen,
due to illegal actions,

1135
01:25:13,417 --> 01:25:16,375
Aaron Hunter is disqualified,

1136
01:25:16,458 --> 01:25:20,875
and the winner
is Borislav "Good Night" Tumbev.

1137
01:25:29,542 --> 01:25:32,583
<i>And as they say,
that's all she wrote.</i>

1138
01:25:32,667 --> 01:25:33,667
<i>Good night.</i>

1139
01:25:35,375 --> 01:25:36,750
<i>That's all she wrote.</i>

1140
01:25:38,792 --> 01:25:40,750
<i>Where did that saying come from, anyway?</i>

1141
01:25:41,708 --> 01:25:43,167
<i>Let tell you the story I heard.</i>

1142
01:25:44,125 --> 01:25:45,375
<i>During the Second World War,</i>

1143
01:25:45,458 --> 01:25:48,375
<i>it wasn't uncommon
for an overseas service man</i>

1144
01:25:48,458 --> 01:25:52,833
<i>to receive a brief, cutting letter
from a girlfriend</i>

1145
01:25:52,917 --> 01:25:55,583
<i>telling him that their romance was over,</i>

1146
01:25:55,667 --> 01:25:58,667
<i>and that she'd found someone else
in his absence.</i>

1147
01:25:59,542 --> 01:26:01,958
<i>When questioned by his buddies,</i>

1148
01:26:02,042 --> 01:26:04,958
<i>the anguished soldier
would give a response</i>

1149
01:26:05,042 --> 01:26:09,417
<i>that became so common
it entered our language</i>

1150
01:26:10,125 --> 01:26:11,833
<i>as meaning "It's over."</i>

1151
01:26:26,375 --> 01:26:30,125
<i>Nowadays, fight commentators
use this in cases just like this.</i>

1152
01:26:31,083 --> 01:26:33,167
<i>I mean, not just like this,</i>

1153
01:26:33,250 --> 01:26:36,333
<i>a freaked out fighter who beats the shit
out of everyone in the ring,</i>

1154
01:26:36,417 --> 01:26:38,875
<i>but a regular knockout.</i>

1155
01:26:39,750 --> 01:26:41,417
<i>Anyway, I think you got the point.</i>

1156
01:27:06,792 --> 01:27:12,583
Yes, mother. No, she's...

1157
01:27:13,500 --> 01:27:19,542
Okay, just calm down. We'll find her.

1158
01:27:19,625 --> 01:27:23,333
I'll bring her back. I promise.

1159
01:27:37,042 --> 01:27:38,875
I really thought he was getting better.

1160
01:27:39,750 --> 01:27:43,083
The strange thing is that
the meds don't work anymore.

1161
01:27:48,167 --> 01:27:50,042
Sorry you had to come all this way, but...

1162
01:27:52,792 --> 01:27:55,583
If it wasn't for me,
Aaron wouldn't be here.

1163
01:28:03,458 --> 01:28:06,125
I'll admit, he doesn't show
any signs of aggression,

1164
01:28:08,542 --> 01:28:11,625
but we need a relative
or a close friend to vouch for him.

1165
01:28:12,208 --> 01:28:14,625
His wife and his manager think
it will be good idea

1166
01:28:14,708 --> 01:28:18,750
for him to stay here a while,
and, quite frankly, I agree with them.

1167
01:28:19,708 --> 01:28:22,833
So I just can't release him to you
because you want me to.

1168
01:28:29,875 --> 01:28:32,208
Are there any cameras here in the office?

1169
01:28:33,708 --> 01:28:35,333
Uh, no.

1170
01:28:42,958 --> 01:28:45,542
Wait, wait! I'm not crazy! Wait.

1171
01:28:48,583 --> 01:28:49,583
Or maybe I am.

1172
01:28:52,667 --> 01:28:53,667
So...

1173
01:28:55,375 --> 01:28:57,417
It's all I won from the fight.
It's in US dollars.

1174
01:28:57,500 --> 01:28:59,333
And it's all I've got, Doc.

1175
01:29:15,833 --> 01:29:17,875
I've been working here 17 years.

1176
01:29:18,542 --> 01:29:21,750
I make sure the "strange" people
don't bother the normal ones.

1177
01:29:22,917 --> 01:29:25,792
The longer I spend with my patients, the...

1178
01:29:25,875 --> 01:29:26,958
the worse I feel.

1179
01:29:30,875 --> 01:29:33,333
Are we normal? Who are we to judge?

1180
01:29:35,292 --> 01:29:39,708
After all, I deeply doubt that any of them
would do what I'm about to do.

1181
01:29:41,792 --> 01:29:44,833
You've been here all morning.
I heard your whole wacked-out story.

1182
01:29:46,000 --> 01:29:47,667
Could you tell me, please,

1183
01:29:47,750 --> 01:29:51,583
why would you waste my time instead
of starting straight off with this?

1184
01:29:54,167 --> 01:29:56,250
<i>* Someone once told me that *</i>

1185
01:29:58,917 --> 01:30:01,792
<i>* Love is often blind *</i>

1186
01:30:02,792 --> 01:30:06,458
<i>* And as I wait for life to pass *</i>

1187
01:30:08,750 --> 01:30:11,458
<i>* I should just take my time *</i>

1188
01:30:12,125 --> 01:30:16,375
<i>* To know that I, I'm just a servant *</i>

1189
01:30:18,750 --> 01:30:21,833
<i>* And I'm listening for my cue *</i>

1190
01:30:22,875 --> 01:30:26,583
<i>* If I'm faithful and I'm certain *</i>

1191
01:30:27,417 --> 01:30:31,042
<i>* I'd be blessed
To sing this song with you *</i>

1192
01:30:42,500 --> 01:30:45,667
<i>* Someone told me about our love *</i>

1193
01:30:48,458 --> 01:30:51,333
<i>* Could chase away the fear *</i>

1194
01:30:52,292 --> 01:30:55,917
<i>* Something from the light above *</i>

1195
01:30:58,292 --> 01:31:01,208
<i>* Whisper like an angel in my ear *</i>

1196
01:31:02,208 --> 01:31:07,292
<i>* That I, I'm just a soul child *</i>

1197
01:31:08,750 --> 01:31:11,542
<i>* Trying to find my way *</i>

1198
01:31:13,708 --> 01:31:16,500
<i>* Searching for a little joy *</i>

1199
01:31:17,458 --> 01:31:21,333
<i>* To spread throughout my day *</i>

1200
01:31:21,417 --> 01:31:27,500
<i>* Ooh, ooh, ooh, *</i>

1201
01:31:32,500 --> 01:31:34,417
<i>* Hey, hey *</i>

1202
01:31:35,458 --> 01:31:38,125
<i>* Alright, yeah *</i>

1203
01:31:46,708 --> 01:31:50,167
<i>* Someone told me have some faith *</i>

1204
01:31:52,125 --> 01:31:55,000
<i>* The creator has a master plan *</i>

1205
01:31:56,250 --> 01:31:59,375
<i>* The truest love should never wait *</i>

1206
01:32:01,708 --> 01:32:04,792
<i>* Let our spirit shine and take a stand *</i>

